"{\n  \"groups\": [\n    {\n      \"questions\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \"She ___ (water) the plants every morning.\\nA) waters  B) water  C) watered\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"A\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"I ___ (just / finish) my report.\\nA) have just finished  B) just have finished  C) just finished\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"A\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Every summer we ___ (go) camping in the forest.\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"go\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"He ___ (live) in this town since 2010.\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"has lived\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Water ___ (boil) at 100°C.\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"B\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"They ___ (already / plant) 200 trees this year.\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"A\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"The river ___ (flow) through the city.\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"flows\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Scientists ___ (discover) a new species of frog last month.\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"have discovered\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"She ___ (never / recycle) plastic bottles before.\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"C\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"The sun ___ (rise) in the east.\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"B\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"I ___ (never / see) such a clear night sky before.\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"have never seen\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Our company ___ (reduce) its carbon emissions each year.\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"B\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Tom ___ (break) his bike yesterday.\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"broke\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Do you ___ (ever / visit) a wildlife reserve?\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"A\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"The forest ___ (be) a home for many animals.\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"is\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"answers\": [\n        \"A\",\n        \"A\",\n        \"go\",\n        \"has lived\",\n        \"B\",\n        \"A\",\n        \"flows\",\n        \"have discovered\",\n        \"C\",\n        \"B\",\n        \"have never seen\",\n        \"B\",\n        \"broke\",\n        \"A\",\n        \"is\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"questions\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Which word means ‘the natural environment where organisms live’? \\nA) ecosystem  B) habitat  C) climate  D) species\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"A\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"What do we call the process of converting waste into reusable material?\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"recycling\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Choose the correct term for ‘a plant that lives for many years’. \\nA) annual  B) perennial  C) biennial  D) deciduous\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"B\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"A word meaning ‘to protect the natural world from harm’.\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"conserve\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Which of the following is a renewable energy source? \\nA) coal  B) oil  C) solar  D) natural gas\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"C\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"The opposite of ‘pollution’ is __________.\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"cleanliness\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Select the word that describes ‘the variety of life in a particular habitat’. \\nA) biodiversity  B) uniformity  C) monotony  D) scarcity\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"A\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"A device that converts sunlight into electricity is called a __________.\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"solar panel\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Which term refers to ‘the gradual increase in Earth’s average temperature’? \\nA) global cooling  B) greenhouse effect  C) global warming  D) ozone depletion\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"C\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"The act of cutting down trees in a large area is called __________.\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"deforestation\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Which word means ‘a small, natural waterway’? \\nA) lake  B) river  C) stream  D) ocean\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"C\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"A synonym for ‘to use less’ is __________.\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"conserve\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Which of these animals is a keystone species? \\nA) rabbit  B) wolf  C) pigeon  D) mouse\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"B\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"The term for “the amount of carbon dioxide emitted into the atmosphere” is __________.\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"carbon footprint\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Which phrase best describes ‘energy that cannot be replenished once used’? \\nA) renewable energy  B) sustainable energy  C) non‑renewable energy  D) green energy\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"C\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"answers\": [\n        \"A\",\n        \"recycling\",\n        \"B\",\n        \"conserve\",\n        \"C\",\n        \"cleanliness\",\n        \"A\",\n        \"solar panel\",\n        \"C\",\n        \"deforestation\",\n        \"C\",\n        \"conserve\",\n        \"B\",\n        \"carbon footprint\",\n        \"C\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"questions\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Fill in the blank with the correct form (Present Simple or Present Perfect):\\nThe city ___ (introduce) a bike‑sharing program last year.\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"has introduced\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Choose the correct verb: \\nWhenever it ___ (rain), the river level rises.\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"A\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Select the right tense for the underlined part:\\n\\\"Scientists ___ (discover) a new method to clean oil spills.\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"B\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Fill in the gap with a word from the ecological vocabulary list:\\n\\\"The ___ of the forest depends on the health of its soil.\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"ecosystem\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Which form is correct?\\n\\\"She ___ (never / see) a sea turtle in the wild before this trip.\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"C\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Complete the sentence using Present Simple:\\n\\\"Birds ___ (migrate) south when winter arrives.\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"migrate\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Choose the proper word:\\n\\\"To ___ energy we need to use solar panels and wind turbines.\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"B\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Fill in the blank with Present Perfect:\\n\\\"We ___ (plant) over 500 saplings this spring.\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"have planted\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Select the correct option:\\n\\\"If you ___ (reduce) waste, the landfill will fill up slower.\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"A\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Insert the appropriate ecological term:\\n\\\"The ____ of the river protects many fish species.\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"habitat\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Choose the right tense:\\n\\\"The government ___ (announce) new climate policies yesterday.\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"D\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Complete with Present Simple:\\n\\\"Electric cars ___ (emit) far less CO₂ than gasoline cars.\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"emit\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Select the correct adjective:\\n\\\"_____ energy sources are essential for sustainable development.\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"B\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Fill in the blank (Present Perfect):\\n\\\"Researchers ___ (study) the impact of micro‑plastics for years.\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"have studied\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Choose the proper verb form:\\n\\\"Each year, volunteers ___ (clean) the beach in June.\\\"\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"B\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"answers\": [\n        \"has introduced\",\n        \"A\",\n        \"B\",\n        \"ecosystem\",\n        \"C\",\n        \"migrate\",\n        \"B\",\n        \"have planted\",\n        \"A\",\n        \"habitat\",\n        \"D\",\n        \"emit\",\n        \"B\",\n        \"have studied\",\n        \"B\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"questions\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \"Read the text below and answer the questions that follow.\\n\\n\\\"Over the past decade, the community of Greenfield ___ (focus) on protecting its local environment. Every morning, residents ___ (walk) through the park, noticing how the river ___ (flow) more clearly after the new filtration system was installed. The council ___ (already / plant) 1,200 native trees since 2015, and the number of birds ___ (increase) noticeably. Volunteers ___ (organise) monthly clean‑up events, and many families ___ (join) these activities for the first time. Scientists ___ (study) the impact of these actions and ___ (find) that air quality has improved significantly. The town ___ (be) proud of its achievements, but they ___ (know) there is still much work to do.\\\"\\n\\n1. Which verb form correctly completes the first blank?\\nA) has focused  B) focused  C) focuses  D) was focusing\\n2. What does the present simple sentence in line 2 tell us about the residents?\\nA) They walked yesterday.\\nB) They walk every morning.\\nC) They will walk tomorrow.\\nD) They are walking now.\\n3. Identify the tense used in the phrase “has already planted”.\\nA) Present Simple\\nB) Present Perfect\\nC) Past Simple\\nD) Future Simple\\n4. Fill in the missing verb for the seventh line (volunteers ___ (organise)).\\n5. What new word in the text means “the natural home of an animal or plant”?\\n6. Choose the correct meaning of “significantly” as used in the passage.\\nA) Slightly  B) Completely  C) To a great extent  D) Unlikely\\n7. Which sentence uses Present Perfect Continuous?\\nA) The river flows more clearly.\\nB) Scientists have studied the impact.\\nC) Volunteers have been organising clean‑up events.\\nD) The town is proud.\\n8. True or False: The community has planted exactly 1,200 trees every year since 2015.\\n9. Which word from the passage is a synonym for “protect”?\\n10. What does the phrase “there is still much work to do” suggest about the future?\\n11. Fill in the blank with the correct form: “The air quality ___ (improve) since the new measures were taken.”\\n12. Identify the part of speech of the word “proud”.\\n13. Which of the following is NOT mentioned as an activity of the volunteers?\\nA) Planting trees\\nB) Organising events\\nC) Monitoring water quality\\nD) Cleaning the beach\\n14. Translate the word “filtration” into Polish.\\n15. Write a short answer (1‑2 sentences) why Present Perfect is used in sentence 5 of the text.\\n\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"A\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"2. What does the present simple sentence in line 2 tell us about the residents?\\nA) They walked yesterday.\\nB) They walk every morning.\\nC) They will walk tomorrow.\\nD) They are walking now.\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"B\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"3. Identify the tense used in the phrase “has already planted”.\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"B\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"4. Fill in the missing verb for the seventh line (volunteers ___ (organise)).\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"organise\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"5. What new word in the text means “the natural home of an animal or plant”?\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"habitat\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"6. Choose the correct meaning of “significantly” as used in the passage.\\nA) Slightly  B) Completely  C) To a great extent  D) Unlikely\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"C\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"7. Which sentence uses Present Perfect Continuous?\\nA) The river flows more clearly.\\nB) Scientists have studied the impact.\\nC) Volunteers have been organising clean‑up events.\\nD) The town is proud.\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"C\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"8. True or False: The community has planted exactly 1,200 trees every year since 2015.\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"False\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"9. Which word from the passage is a synonym for “protect”?\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"protecting\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"10. What does the phrase “there is still much work to do” suggest about the future?\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"Further actions are needed\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"11. Fill in the blank with the correct form: “The air quality ___ (improve) since the new measures were taken.”\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"has improved\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"12. Identify the part of speech of the word “proud”.\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"adjective\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"13. Which of the following is NOT mentioned as an activity of the volunteers?\\nA) Planting trees\\nB) Organising events\\nC) Monitoring water quality\\nD) Cleaning the beach\",\n          \"type\": \"multiple_choice\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"C\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"14. Translate the word “filtration” into Polish.\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"filtracja\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"15. Write a short answer (1‑2 sentences) why Present Perfect is used in sentence 5 of the text.\",\n          \"type\": \"open_ended\",\n          \"correct_answer\": \"It shows an action that started in the past and has relevance now – the number of birds has increased up to the present.\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"answers\": [\n        \"A\",\n        \"B\",\n        \"B\",\n        \"organise\",\n        \"habitat\",\n        \"C\",\n        \"C\",\n        \"False\",\n        \"protecting\",\n        \"Further actions are needed\",\n        \"has improved\",\n        \"adjective\",\n        \"C\",\n        \"filtracja\",\n        \"It shows an action that started in the past and has relevance now – the number of birds has increased up to the present.\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}"